The reality is that our policy makers failed to recognize the risks associated with the severity of Covid-19. While we can argue about motivation - that is factual and the delay in taking the threat seriously has jeopardized the health of Americans and our economy (and markets).

I just dont understand why @realdonaldtrump and many of his supporters don't recoil at his tweets/words and, instead, are critical of my (and others) constant reminders of his lack of leadership as if his behavior is "normal." Were the appointment of conservative judges a

worthwhile Faustian bargain as we watch our economy and our markets in chaos and heading into a deepening recession? Has he no common sense and good judgment or are his attacks on any opponent now acceptable to so many? Does he not see the bigger crisis picture?

This is a mainstream crisis which must be attacked - not a time in which you attack Biden or whoever disagrees with your policy? @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney Look in the mirror. You and only you failed to understand the severity of Covid-19. You were
sleeping, not Joe Biden.

I find it truly remarkable (and though I am repeating myself as @realdonaldtrump is in his multiple tweets) that amid a spreading virus and economic/stock market chaos you tweet five times last night on Joe Biden, your likely opponent. What is wrong with you? I think we all know.
